51790.name: Acornbearer
51790.text: Deathrattle: Add two 1/1 Squirrels to your hand.
51790.flavorText: You’d be nuts to mess with the squirrel squad.

52058.name: Aranasi Broodmother
52058.text: Taunt When you draw this, restore 4 Health to your hero.
52058.flavorText: She's got a big brood and a big mood.

52072.name: Arcane Fletcher
52072.text: Whenever you play a 1-Cost minion, draw a spell from your deck.
52072.flavorText: Stop trying to make fletch happen. It's not going to happen.

52292.name: Arcane Servant
52292.flavorText: "Would sir like me to punch something?"

52654.name: Arcane Watcher
52654.text: Can't attack unless you have Spell Damage.
52654.flavorText: Now his watch has ended… until you have Spell Damage.

52119.name: Arch-Villain Rafaam
52119.text: Taunt Battlecry: Replace your hand and deck with Legendary minions.
52119.flavorText: Minions must wash hands before being LIQUIDATED AND REPLACED BY SOMEONE BETTER.

52870.name: Archivist Elysiana
52870.text: Battlecry: Discover 5 cards. Replace your deck with 2 copies of each.
52870.flavorText: Your deck is just another organizational challenge to her.

52438.name: Archmage Vargoth
52438.text: At the end of your turn, cast a spell you've cast this turn (targets are random).
52438.flavorText: He's an archmage, but he might want to brush up on the basics... like aiming.

52415.name: Azerite Elemental
52415.text: At the start of your turn, gain Spell Damage +2.

52413.name: Barista Lynchen
52413.text: Battlecry: Add a copy of each of your other Battlecry minions to your hand.

53251.name: Batterhead
53251.text: Rush. After this attacks and kills a minion, it may attack again.
53251.flavorText: When it comes to problem-solving, he always uses his head.

52420.name: Big Bad Archmage
52420.text: At the end of your turn, summon a random 6-Cost minion.
52420.flavorText: "My, my, what big minions I have!"

51739.name: Blastmaster Boom
51739.text: Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Boom Bots for each Bomb in your opponent's deck.
51739.flavorText: He's gonna fly through the air with the greatest of grease.

51757.name: Bronze Herald
51757.text: Deathrattle: Add two 4/4 Dragons to your hand.
51757.flavorText: This is why you shouldn’t shoot the messenger.

52660.name: Call to Adventure
52660.text: Draw the lowest Cost minion from your deck. Give it +2/+2.
52660.flavorText: Even the smallest minion can change the outcome of the game.

52627.name: Catrina Muerte
52627.text: At the end of your turn, resurrect another friendly Undead minion.
52627.flavorText: She always manages to lift your spirits.

52434.name: Chef Nomi
52434.text: Battlecry: If your deck is empty, summon six 6/6 Greasefire Elementals.
52434.flavorText: His cooking is always very well done.

51735.name: Clockwork Goblin
51735.text: Battlecry: Shuffle a Bomb into your opponent's deck. When drawn, it explodes for 5 damage.

52500.name: Commander Rhyssa
52500.flavorText: Two people can keep a secret as long as neither of them are Commander Rhyssa.

51971.name: Conjurer's Calling
51971.text: Twinspell Destroy a minion. Summon 2 minions of the same Cost to replace it.
51971.flavorText: If only you’d let it go to voicemail…

51714.name: Convincing Infiltrator
51714.flavorText: It’s always nice to steal a familiar face.

51769.name: Crystal Power
51769.text: Choose One - Deal 2 damage to a minion; or Restore 5 Health.
51769.flavorText: Often used as healing crystals, but also good for throwing at people.

53179.name: Crystal Stag
53179.text: Rush. Battlecry: If you've restored 5 Health this game, summon a copy of this. ( left!) (Ready!)
53179.flavorText: Arrives alone, but usually leaves with a friend just like him.

51781.name: Crystalsong Portal
51781.text: Discover a Druid minion. If your hand has no minions, keep all 3.
51781.flavorText: Experience the draw of the wild!

52679.name: Daring Escape
52679.text: Return all friendly minions to your hand.
52679.flavorText: Impossible to cast without cackling evilly.

51966.name: Darkest Hour
51966.text: Destroy all friendly minions. For each one, summon a random minion from your deck.
51966.flavorText: It's always darkest just before you find the light switch.

51705.name: Desperate Measures
51705.flavorText: Desperate times call for disparate secrets.

51734.name: Dimensional Ripper
51734.text: Summon 2 copies of a minion in your deck.
51734.flavorText: The first dimensional ripper had a point. The second fell flat. The THIRD one really started to take shape!

51372.name: Dr. Boom's Scheme
51372.flavorText: “We did it! We blew up the vault!” “You mean the vault door?” “Oh. The doooor…”

51761.name: Dragon Speaker
51761.text: Battlecry: Give all Dragons in your hand +3/+3.
51761.flavorText: All of his speeches really drag on.

52810.name: Dreamway Guardians
52810.flavorText: They're a nightmare to deal with.

52742.name: Duel!
52742.text: Summon a minion from each player's deck. They fight!
52742.flavorText: If you don’t fight to the death, it’s Duel Yielding.

51380.name: EVIL Cable Rat
51380.flavorText: Gradually driven to darkness by the promise of unobtainable cheese.

52109.name: EVIL Conscripter
52109.flavorText: Kobold! There’s a place you can handle I said kobold! When you’re short in the candle Cast a spell with the E! V! I! L!

52872.name: EVIL Genius
52872.text: Battlecry: Destroy a friendly minion to add 2 random Lackeys to your hand.
52872.flavorText: You do not want to be on the business end of this intellect!

52111.name: EVIL Miscreant
52111.text: Combo: Add two random Lackeys to your hand.
52111.flavorText: Because there are no G.O.O.D. Miscreants.

52482.name: Eager Underling
52482.flavorText: Eager to please, even if it kills him.

53218.name: Exotic Mountseller
53218.text: Whenever you cast a spell, summon a random 3-Cost Beast.
53218.flavorText: *Taps roof of mammoth* “You can fit so many squirrels in this thing!”

52936.name: Faceless Rager
52936.flavorText: When you need to rage anonymously.

52873.name: Fel Lord Betrug
52873.text: Whenever you draw a minion, summon a copy with Rush that dies at end of turn.

52940.name: Flight Master
52940.text: Battlecry: Summon a 2/2 Gryphon for each player.
52940.flavorText: Your gryphon will be summoned following a brief safety demonstration.

52632.name: Forbidden Words
52632.text: Spend all your Mana. Destroy a minion with that much Attack or less.
52632.flavorText: Please confirm your age before reading this flavor text.

51373.name: Hagatha's Scheme
51373.text: Deal 1 damage to all minions. (Upgrades each turn!)
51373.flavorText: "All shall suffer!" "But Hagatha, those are your minions..." "I said ALL!!!"

51733.name: Hecklebot
51733.text: Taunt Battlecry: Your opponent summons a minion from their deck.
51733.flavorText: Built by goblins, designed by a troll.

52114.name: Heistbaron Togwaggle
52114.text: Battlecry: If you control a Lackey, choose a fantastic treasure.
52114.flavorText: A staunch ally of Rafaam, at least while the shinies keep flowing.

52112.name: Hench-Clan Burglar
52112.flavorText: She’s more of a rat burglar.

52287.name: Hench-Clan Hag
52287.text: Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Amalgams with all minion types.
52287.flavorText: The Hench Clan is an equal opportunity employer, no matter which parts of you came from where.

52935.name: Hench-Clan Hogsteed
52935.flavorText: This is CLEARLY their first rodeo.

51715.name: Hench-Clan Shadequill
51715.text: Deathrattle: Restore 5 Health to the enemy hero.

52290.name: Hench-Clan Sneak
52290.flavorText: He’d be a lot sneakier if he wasn’t trailing 300 yards of power cable…

52479.name: Heroic Innkeeper
52479.text: Taunt. Battlecry: Gain +2/+2 for each other friendly minion.
52479.flavorText: We reserve the right to refuse service to any 1/1.

53099.name: Hunting Party
53099.text: Copy all Beasts in your hand.
53099.flavorText: Not sure I’d call it a good party if everyone ends up beside themselves.

52871.name: Impferno
52871.text: Give your Demons +1 Attack. Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions.
52871.flavorText: Imps don't get mad when you set them on fire. They think it's cozy.

53124.name: Improve Morale
53124.text: Deal 1 damage to a minion. If it survives, add a Lackey to your hand.
53124.flavorText: "The beatings will continue until MY morale improves."

52954.name: Jepetto Joybuzz
52954.text: Battlecry: Draw 2 minions from your deck. Set their Attack, Health, and Cost to 1.

52480.name: Jumbo Imp
52480.text: Costs (1) less whenever a friendly Demon dies while this is in your hand.
52480.flavorText: Jumbo in size! Huge in E.V.I.L.!

53002.name: Kalecgos
53002.text: Your first spell each turn costs (0). Battlecry: Discover a spell.
53002.flavorText: He was once the Aspect of Magic but gave it up to focus on cheap tricks.

52809.name: Keeper Stalladris
52809.text: After you cast a Choose One spell, add copies of both choices to your hand.

52502.name: Khadgar
52502.text: Your cards that summon minions summon twice as many.
52502.flavorText: "What do you call two minions summoned at once? Twinions, haha! Wait... where are you going?"

51376.name: Lazul's Scheme
51376.text: Reduce the Attack of an enemy minion by 1 until your next turn. (Upgrades each turn!)
51376.flavorText: "What's that you're dreaming? You're weak and you're screaming! It must be my scheming..."

51791.name: Lifeweaver
51791.text: Whenever you restore Health, add a random Druid spell to your hand.
51791.flavorText: Lifeweaving is all well and good until it's time to cut the thread.

52490.name: Lightforged Blessing
52490.flavorText: Some might call this a lightforgery.

51795.name: Lucentbark
51795.text: Taunt Deathrattle: Go Dormant. Restore 5 Health to awaken this minion.
51795.flavorText: Always feels refreshed after a little dirt nap.

52950.name: Mad Summoner
52950.text: Battlecry: Fill each player's board with 1/1 Imps.
52950.flavorText: Does he summon because of his madness, or is he mad from all the summoning?

52715.name: Madame Lazul
52715.text: Battlecry: Discover a copy of a card in your opponent's hand.
52715.flavorText: Of course she knows the future, she’s been looking at your cards the WHOLE TIME!

53173.name: Magic Carpet
53173.text: After you play a 1-Cost minion, give it +1 Attack and Rush.
53173.flavorText: Its small yet fierce riders are affectionately known as rug rats.

51977.name: Magic Dart Frog
51977.text: After you cast a spell, deal 1 damage to a random enemy minion.
51977.flavorText: There's a powerful throat in this frog.

52991.name: Magic Trick
52991.text: Discover a spell that costs (3) or less.
52991.flavorText: The world is not ready for an illusion of this depth and intricacy!

52706.name: Mana Cyclone
52706.text: Battlecry: For each spell you've cast this turn, add a random Mage spell to your hand.
52706.flavorText: It'll put a good spin on your spells.

52942.name: Mana Reservoir
52942.flavorText: If it soaks too long, it becomes a reservoir hog.

52070.name: Marked Shot
52070.text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. Discover a spell.

52633.name: Mass Resurrection
52633.text: Summon 3 friendly minions that died this game.
52633.flavorText: One's company, two's a crowd, and three's a “mass” resurrection, apparently.

51943.name: Messenger Raven
51943.flavorText: You can make a collect CAW!

51727.name: Muckmorpher
51727.text: Battlecry: Transform into a 4/4 copy of a different minion in your deck.
51727.flavorText: Fan favorite in the muck morphin' sewer strangers.

52148.name: Mutate
52148.text: Transform a friendly minion into a random one that costs (1) more.
52148.flavorText: You'll get the transformation you want when murlocs fly.

52496.name: Mysterious Blade
52496.text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, gain +1 Attack.
52496.flavorText: It knows every secret you have left.

52494.name: Never Surrender!
52494.text: Secret: When your opponent casts a spell, give your minions +2 Health.

52082.name: Nine Lives
52082.text: Discover a friendly Deathrattle minion that died this game. Also trigger its Deathrattle.
52082.flavorText: Beware the night of the living pets!

52685.name: Nozari
52685.text: Battlecry: Restore both heroes to full Health.
52685.flavorText: In another timeline, she was called Yeszari.

52081.name: Oblivitron
52081.text: Deathrattle: Summon a Mech from your hand and trigger its Deathrattle.

53138.name: Omega Devastator
53138.text: Battlecry: If you have 10 Mana Crystals, deal 10 damage to a minion.
53138.flavorText: The Alpha Devastator didn’t devastate enough. The Beta Devastator devastated too much. But the Omega was just right!

52698.name: Plot Twist
52698.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Draw that many cards.
52698.flavorText: It’s coming from inside the deck!

52707.name: Portal Keeper
52707.text: Battlecry: Shuffle 3 Portals into your deck. When drawn, summon a 2/2 Demon with Rush.
52707.flavorText: No longer allowed to be “it” when playing demon tag.

52486.name: Portal Overfiend
52486.text: Battlecry: Shuffle 3 Portals into your deck. When drawn, summon a 2/2 Demon with Rush.
52486.flavorText: It’s like an interdimensional game of demon tag.

52312.name: Potion Vendor
52312.text: Battlecry: Restore 2 Health to all friendly characters.
52312.flavorText: Everyone gets two because that’s all she can hold.

52640.name: Power of Creation
52640.text: Discover a 6-Cost minion. Summon two copies of it.
52640.flavorText: Mostly used for party tricks, to be honest.

52418.name: Proud Defender
52418.text: Taunt Has +2 Attack while you have no other minions.
52418.flavorText: It'll take a humble offender to defeat him.

52639.name: Ray of Frost
52639.text: Twinspell Freeze a minion. If it's already Frozen, deal 2 damage to it.
52639.flavorText: If you have zero chill, this can help.

52943.name: Recurring Villain
52943.text: Deathrattle: If this minion has 4 or more Attack, resummon it.
52943.flavorText: Mwahahaha! You'll never catch him this time!

52288.name: Safeguard
52288.flavorText: Keep it secret. Keep it safeguarded!

52636.name: Scargil
52636.flavorText: Wanna know how he got those scars? So does he.

51567.name: Shadowy Figure
51567.text: Battlecry: Transform into a 2/2 copy of a friendly Deathrattle minion.
51567.flavorText: Terrible at shadow puppets: “This is… a tentacle! And this is… two tentacles!”

52894.name: Shimmerfly
52894.text: Deathrattle: Add a random Hunter spell to your hand.
52894.flavorText: Plenty of buzz around this card.

52422.name: Sludge Slurper
52422.flavorText: You can't stop slurping this delicious sludge!

53171.name: Soldier of Fortune
53171.text: Whenever this minion attacks, give your opponent a Coin.

52468.name: Soul of the Murloc
52468.text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Murloc."

52289.name: Spellbook Binder
52289.text: Battlecry: If you have Spell Damage, draw a card.
52289.flavorText: You're bound to love his work!

52281.name: Spellward Jeweler
52281.text: Battlecry: Your hero is Elusive until next turn.
52281.flavorText: The fanciest possible way of distracting enemies with shiny things.

52307.name: Sunreaver Warmage
52307.text: Battlecry: If you're holding a spell that costs (5) or more, deal 4 damage.
52307.flavorText: What, did you expect the Sunreavers to be coldages?

52409.name: Swampqueen Hagatha
52409.text: Battlecry: Add a 5/5 Horror to your hand. Teach it two Shaman spells.
52409.flavorText: Rafaam mainly enjoys working with Hagatha because she never laughs at Dr. Boom's jokes.

51737.name: Sweeping Strikes
51737.text: Give a minion "Also damages minions next to whomever this attacks."

52616.name: Tak Nozwhisker
52616.text: Whenever you shuffle a card into your deck, add a copy to your hand.
52616.flavorText: "One for me and one for future me!"

52086.name: The Boom Reaver
52086.text: Battlecry: Summon a copy of a minion in your deck. Give it Rush.

52819.name: The Forest's Aid
52819.flavorText: Delicious Forest’s Aid! Made from real forests.

51375.name: Togwaggle's Scheme
51375.text: Choose a minion. Shuffle 1 (copy, copies) of it into your deck. (Upgrades each turn!)
51375.flavorText: "Many minions equals many treasures for king. Kobold arithmetic!"

52277.name: Toxfin
52277.flavorText: I'm addicted to him, but I know that he's Toxfin.

52278.name: Traveling Healer
52278.flavorText: Some heroes have soft hearts and hard shells.

53249.name: Tunnel Blaster
53249.flavorText: And you always thought they wore the candles just for fun.

51724.name: Underbelly Angler
51724.text: After you play a Murloc, add a random Murloc to your hand.

52603.name: Underbelly Fence
52603.text: Battlecry: If you're holding a card from another class, gain +1/+1 and Rush.
52603.flavorText: She’ll take anything you have—except scruples and a good work ethic.

52417.name: Underbelly Ooze
52417.text: After this minion survives damage, summon a copy of it.
52417.flavorText: It's always accepting of the less successful adventurers.

51827.name: Unidentified Contract
51827.text: Destroy a minion. Gains a bonus effect in your hand.
51827.flavorText: The terms of service are constantly changing.

52089.name: Unleash the Beast
52089.flavorText: The Kirin Tor have always been lax in enforcing leash laws.

52306.name: Unseen Saboteur
52306.text: Battlecry: Your opponent casts a random spell from their hand (targets chosen randomly).
52306.flavorText: Far more effective than the flamboyant saboteur.

51847.name: Unsleeping Soul
51847.text: Silence a friendly minion, then summon a copy of it.
51847.flavorText: It's 3 am. Do you know where your soul is?

52790.name: Ursatron
52790.text: Deathrattle: Draw a Mech from your deck.
52790.flavorText: It's been programmed to include all the bear necessities.

52606.name: Vendetta
52606.text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. Costs (0) if you're holding a card from another class.
52606.flavorText: A vengeful and vicarious vanguard against violent villains or vexed victims.

52091.name: Vereesa Windrunner
52091.flavorText: Good things come in threes: Windrunner sisters and arrows of Thori'dal.

53104.name: Vicious Scraphound
53104.text: Whenever this minion deals damage, gain that much Armor.

52295.name: Violet Spellsword
52295.text: Battlecry: Gain +1 Attack for each spell in your hand.
52295.flavorText: If you have to wield a spell and a sword, then neither is performing to expectation.

52296.name: Violet Warden
52296.flavorText: He's got magic, a shield, and an unwavering obsession with the color purple.

52617.name: Waggle Pick
52617.text: Deathrattle: Return a random friendly minion to your hand. It costs (2) less.
52617.flavorText: Kobolds informally refer to its effect as a deathwaggle.

51722.name: Walking Fountain
51722.flavorText: The weirdest part is that it doesn't have legs.

52902.name: Whirlwind Tempest
52902.flavorText: And your minions with mega-windfury get... dizzy.

51738.name: Wrenchcalibur
51738.text: After your hero attacks, shuffle a Bomb into your opponent's deck.
51738.flavorText: Whoso pulleth out this wrench from the toolbox is rightwise king of the lab.

56047.name: Zayle, Shadow Cloak
56047.text: You start the game with one of Zayle's EVIL Decks!
